# Technical Master Document (TMD)

## Architecture
My Bingo Mixer is a single-page web application built on:
- React for UI rendering
- TypeScript for static typing and safety
- Vite for fast development and build tooling

The app is structured as a simple component tree with a single main entry point (`src/App.tsx`) and supporting styling in `src/style.css`.

## Components
- `src/main.tsx`: application bootstrap and root rendering
- `src/App.tsx`: the primary app component containing game logic, prompt input, and card UI
- `src/style.css`: theme styles and responsive layout

## State and Behavior
### Game state
- `prompts`: deck of prompt strings
- `card`: current 5x5 bingo card content
- `selected`: boolean state for each square, including pre-marked free space
- `lastShuffled`: timestamp for the latest card mix
- `customPrompt`: user input for new prompts

### Business logic
- `buildCard(prompts)`: generates a new randomized bingo card with a center free space
- `toggleCell(index)`: marks or unmarks a card cell during play
- `bingoLines`: computed win patterns for rows, columns, diagonals, and future four-corners support

## Persistence
The app stores state in `localStorage` to preserve:
- prompt deck
- current card configuration
- selected tiles
- last shuffle timestamp

## Test gate and CI
A workspace-scoped stop hook has been added at `.github/hooks/stop-test-gate.json`.
- It runs `npm test` before an agent completes.
- `npm test` currently runs `npm run build`.

### Build and validation scripts
- `npm run dev`: start local development server
- `npm run build`: compile TypeScript and build production assets
- `npm run preview`: preview production build locally
- `npm run lint`: lint source files
- `npm run typecheck`: run TypeScript type checking
- `npm test`: execute the build as the safety gate

## Deployment
The application is configured for GitHub Pages deployment via `.github/workflows/pages.yml`.

A Docker deployment flow is now available with `Dockerfile`, `.dockerignore`, and `docker-compose.yml`.
A GitHub Actions workflow for Azure container deployment is also included at `.github/workflows/azure-container-deploy.yml`.

## Lima VM support
A Lima VM configuration is available in `lima/default.yaml` for optional local development using Ubuntu-based VMs. The environment installs Node.js, Docker, and Podman, and forwards port `4173` for the Vite dev server.

## Extension points
### New features
- Add new bingo patterns such as Four Corners with TDD-backed tests
- Add a dedicated play mode UI / card draw UX
- Add share/export of card decks
- Add multi-theme prompt decks and selection controls

### Custom agents and automation
- `.github/agents/quiz-master.agent.md`: custom Quiz Master agent prompt for generating Bingo quiz content
- `.github/instructions/design-guide.instructions.md`: design-first guidance for UI work

## Open Source and Documentation
This document aims to be a technical anchor for contributors.
- keep explanations clear and concrete
- link feature goals to implementation details
- keep the repository easy to navigate for developers and reviewers
